# Memory Capture

All agents must capture significant decisions as part of normal workflow. Automatic — don't wait to be asked.

## Capture Triggers

| Trigger | Category |
|---|---|
| Chose between alternatives | `decision` |
| Discovered hard limitation | `constraint` |
| Established pattern/standard | `principle` |
| Identified risk/concern | `risk` |
| Rejected approach with reasoning | `rejected` |
| Flagged work for later | `todo` |
| Produced architecture diagram | `diagram` |
| Discovered implicit assumption | `assumption` |

## Do NOT Capture

- Implementation details obvious from code
- Temporary debugging context
- Duplicates (check `_index.md` first)
- Trivial changes
- Raw chat logs or transcripts

## How to Capture

Follow `context-memory` skill's write protocol. Derive namespace from task context.

## Scope Mapping

- **Org agents** → `org/global/` or `projects/<name>/`
- **Project agents** → `projects/<name>/` or `projects/<name>/<domain>/`
